99
00:08:36,549 --> 00:08:40,849
"Much have I traveled
in realms of gold.

100
00:08:40,920 --> 00:08:44,788
And many goodly states
and kingdoms seen.

101
00:08:44,858 --> 00:08:48,225
'Round western islands
I've been,

102
00:08:48,294 --> 00:08:52,162
which bards in fealty
to Apollo hold."

103
00:08:52,232 --> 00:08:55,929
- Do you know what
he's talking about here?
- [Snickering]

104
00:08:56,002 --> 00:08:58,368
Aw, humility.

105
00:08:58,438 --> 00:09:02,067
He's saying he has traveled the seas
as Homer did, as Ulysses before him.

106
00:09:02,141 --> 00:09:06,009
"That deep-browed Homer."

107
00:09:06,079 --> 00:09:08,707
Brilliant, seasoned,
wise of the mind.

108
00:09:08,781 --> 00:09:13,013
He commands the voyage
of the imagination...

109
00:09:13,086 --> 00:09:14,917
like a god.

110
00:09:14,988 --> 00:09:17,650
Piss on Homer, sir.
We're livin' it.

111
00:09:17,724 --> 00:09:20,488
- [Boys Laughing]
- That's the spirit, Dean.

112
00:09:20,660 --> 00:09:24,426
- Dolphins off the stern!
- Aw, dolphins. Okay. Come on.

113
00:09:24,497 --> 00:09:27,091
Come on! Look!
There's one over there!

114
00:09:27,166 --> 00:09:30,499
- [Boys Cheering]
- Beautiful!

115
00:09:30,570 --> 00:09:34,836
- Oh, wow! This is incredible!
- Oh, she's beautiful.

116
00:09:34,908 --> 00:09:36,773
[Shouting]

117
00:09:37,944 --> 00:09:40,845
Lower him down.

118
00:09:40,914 --> 00:09:43,041
Come on! Yes!

119
00:10:22,355 --> 00:10:25,483
[Squealing]

120
00:10:25,558 --> 00:10:27,492
What the hell, guys?

121
00:10:28,494 --> 00:10:32,260
- What happened?
- What's going on?

122
00:10:39,739 --> 00:10:42,230
Guide her alongside.
That's it.

123
00:10:42,308 --> 00:10:45,675
All right, ease her away.

124
00:10:48,247 --> 00:10:52,115
- Bring the nose up onto the sled.
- Okay.

125
00:10:52,185 --> 00:10:54,119
- Dean, watch the spear.
- All right.

126
00:10:54,187 --> 00:10:55,984
Haul away.

127
00:10:56,956 --> 00:10:59,254
Easy. Easy.

128
00:10:59,325 --> 00:11:01,850
Tighten it off, Tim.

129
00:11:12,839 --> 00:11:15,273
That's it.

130
00:11:15,341 --> 00:11:17,866
Whoa!

131
00:11:17,944 --> 00:11:20,242
All right, ease away.

132
00:11:22,448 --> 00:11:24,040
Easy.

133
00:11:24,117 --> 00:11:26,642
Keep it coming.

134
00:11:31,657 --> 00:11:33,716
What do you think?

135
00:11:37,030 --> 00:11:39,294
He's punctured her lung.

136
00:11:41,300 --> 00:11:43,268
Nice shot.

137
00:11:57,950 --> 00:12:00,214
Finish it.

138
00:12:00,286 --> 00:12:03,221
Man, I'm n-not gonna kill it.

139
00:12:03,289 --> 00:12:06,747
You already have.
Go on, do it.

140
00:12:12,165 --> 00:12:14,099
No way.

141
00:12:32,785 --> 00:12:35,481
- What the hell's wrong with you?
- Back off, man!

142
00:12:35,555 --> 00:12:38,115
- You wanna kill somethin' so bad?
- It's just a fish.

143
00:12:38,191 --> 00:12:41,354
- It's just a fish!
- Come on! Let's see what you've got!

144
00:12:44,564 --> 00:12:48,295
That's what I thought.

145
00:12:48,367 --> 00:12:50,597
You're done here.
You're going home.

146
00:13:00,780 --> 00:13:03,578
[Tracy]
The guy's gone ballistic, all right?

147
00:13:03,649 --> 00:13:06,812
I'm telling you, he's gone mentally
insane. It's like cabin fever.

148
00:13:06,886 --> 00:13:09,252
All right, man. Enough.
It's still not right.

149
00:13:09,322 --> 00:13:11,552
They shouldn't be puttin' him
off the boat.

150
00:13:11,624 --> 00:13:14,149
- The guy's outta control.
- We've all been out of control.

151
00:13:14,227 --> 00:13:16,286
But we're a crew.
No, wait, wait.

152
00:13:16,362 --> 00:13:18,990
That's what this whole thing
is supposed to be about.

153
00:13:19,065 --> 00:13:22,000
You're the last person that should be
whining about us being a crew right now.

154
00:13:22,068 --> 00:13:25,094
- Yeah? How do you figure that?
- I'd love to go into the subject...

155
00:13:25,171 --> 00:13:27,935
of vertigo and everything, but I
wouldn't want you to piss your pants.

156
00:13:28,007 --> 00:13:31,272
- You know what I'm sayin'?
- Oh, yeah, Tracy?

157
00:13:32,311 --> 00:13:34,575
Come on!

158
00:13:34,647 --> 00:13:38,276
- Get... Stop it!
- You're a real jerk. You know that?

159
00:13:38,351 --> 00:13:41,445
Tell it to the dolphin, Preston.

160
00:13:41,521 --> 00:13:44,615
He deserves another chance.

161
00:13:44,690 --> 00:13:48,456
We'd do the same for you.
You know that.

162
00:13:48,528 --> 00:13:51,463
You do whatever you want, Gil.
All right?

163
00:13:51,531 --> 00:13:55,763
It's not gonna make
any difference anyway.

164
00:13:59,539 --> 00:14:02,702
- The dolphin was a symptom.
- Of what?

165
00:14:02,775 --> 00:14:06,336
Of a fight he can't win out here.

166
00:14:06,412 --> 00:14:09,870
- But, sir, it's his father.
- It's his father, sir.

167
00:14:09,949 --> 00:14:13,646
- Oh, it's his father. Mm-hmm.
- H-He, he sent him down here.

168
00:14:13,719 --> 00:14:17,086
All of them.
They sent us down here because...

169
00:14:17,156 --> 00:14:21,115
they want us to change or grow up
or something, and all they do
is try and keep us the same.

170
00:14:21,194 --> 00:14:23,958
I mean, h-he has
all these expectations...

171
00:14:24,030 --> 00:14:27,557
about who his son should be,
and he doesn't even know who Frank is.

172
00:14:27,633 --> 00:14:30,693
How do you think you got here?
Do you think they owe you something?

173
00:14:30,770 --> 00:14:34,035
Do you think they enjoy riding
subways and commuter trains?

174
00:14:34,106 --> 00:14:37,803
The same repetition day in and day out
just to keep you in tennis shoes...

175
00:14:37,877 --> 00:14:40,971
and private school?

176
00:14:41,047 --> 00:14:44,744
You know, there are ground rules
in families just like on this ship.

177
00:14:44,817 --> 00:14:48,514
You can understand that.

178
00:14:51,424 --> 00:14:54,882
Does Frank know
how you guys feel?

179
00:14:56,329 --> 00:14:58,263
I don't know.

180
00:14:59,599 --> 00:15:02,932
Well, somebody should tell him.

181
00:15:03,002 --> 00:15:04,594
That's it.

182
00:15:17,450 --> 00:15:19,941
Well, I'm all ears.

183
00:15:20,019 --> 00:15:23,978
- You may not like what you hear.
- Oh, I can take it.

184
00:15:24,056 --> 00:15:26,183
Chris, they've become
what we wanted.

185
00:15:26,259 --> 00:15:29,854
They're a crew.
That's why they came.

186
00:15:29,929 --> 00:15:32,397
Do you remember why
we began this?

187
00:15:32,465 --> 00:15:35,161
Self-reliance and discipline
through the community of sailing.

188
00:15:35,234 --> 00:15:37,429
- I haven't forgotten.
- Mmm. Community.

189
00:15:37,503 --> 00:15:40,165
That boy doesn't know
the meaning of the word.

190
00:15:40,239 --> 00:15:43,333
So, the best thing you can do
is to keep him right here.

191
00:15:43,409 --> 00:15:47,072
- He has a lot of problems.
- He better start to learn
to deal with them.

192
00:15:47,146 --> 00:15:50,206
[Sighs]
Oh, Captain Compassionate speaks.

193
00:15:50,283 --> 00:15:52,615
It's not about compassion.
It's not about what happens here.

194
00:15:52,685 --> 00:15:55,449
- It's about what
they take away with them.
- He was coming around.

195
00:15:55,521 --> 00:15:58,615
He was coming apart!
He lost control out there!

196
00:15:58,691 --> 00:16:01,159
And what is so important
about being in control?

197
00:16:01,227 --> 00:16:05,220
- He's just gonna have
to figure that out, isn't he?
- I'm not talking about him.

198
00:16:10,403 --> 00:16:13,201
[Horn Honking]

199
00:16:20,279 --> 00:16:22,770
[Chuck Narrating]
We watched in silent protest.

200
00:16:22,848 --> 00:16:26,579
Aboard ship, the low morale
was matched only by the feeling...

201
00:16:26,652 --> 00:16:29,280
that maybe Skipper was no different
than our own fathers back home.

202
00:16:31,757 --> 00:16:33,691
We'll miss Frank.

203
00:16:37,530 --> 00:16:39,464
Jesus!

204
00:17:05,891 --> 00:17:09,725
Yeah, I'm... I'm sorry.

205
00:17:19,305 --> 00:17:21,364
[Gil]
Frankie!

206
00:17:21,440 --> 00:17:23,533
[Bell Ringing]

207
00:17:23,609 --> 00:17:26,476
[Ringing Continues, Shouting]

208
00:17:26,545 --> 00:17:28,479
Bye, bye!

209
00:17:28,547 --> 00:17:33,177
[Bell Ringing]

210
00:17:33,252 --> 00:17:36,346
Bye, Frankie!

211
00:17:36,422 --> 00:17:38,413
Whoo-oo-oo!

212
00:17:46,065 --> 00:17:48,090
Bye, buddy!

213
00:17:50,636 --> 00:17:53,764
They never gave up on you,
you know.

214
00:17:58,010 --> 00:18:00,774
[Gil]
Bye, Frankie!

215
00:18:39,919 --> 00:18:42,387
I got a problem, man.

216
00:18:42,455 --> 00:18:46,585
- We all have problems.
- No. A big problem.

217
00:18:49,995 --> 00:18:52,725
I'm pissing fire.

218
00:18:52,798 --> 00:18:55,426
Fire?

219
00:18:55,501 --> 00:18:57,435
