to identify ourselves.

245
00:20:50,149 --> 00:20:53,778
Tell them we're the American
school ship Albatross.

246
00:20:53,852 --> 00:20:57,788
Use your best
Puerto Rican accent.

247
00:20:57,856 --> 00:21:02,190
[Spanish]

248
00:21:02,261 --> 00:21:04,456
[Spanish]

249
00:21:04,530 --> 00:21:07,658
[Girard] They think we're
carrying Cuban refugees, Captain.

250
00:21:07,733 --> 00:21:10,133
I don't think they're going to take it
lightly that I'm a Cuban national.

251
00:21:10,202 --> 00:21:14,002
Nothing's going to happen.
Remind them that according
to the Geneva Convention...

252
00:21:14,073 --> 00:21:18,305
firing on citizens on the high seas
is an act of war.

253
00:21:18,377 --> 00:21:22,871
[Spanish]

254
00:21:22,948 --> 00:21:27,817
They say they're acting
on the direct order of Fidel Castro.

255
00:21:27,886 --> 00:21:33,017
[Spanish]

256
00:21:33,092 --> 00:21:35,560
[Continues In Spanish]

257
00:21:37,596 --> 00:21:39,496
Tell them to come aboard.

258
00:21:39,565 --> 00:21:42,898
Do it! Come on!

259
00:21:42,968 --> 00:21:46,028
[Spanish]

260
00:21:46,105 --> 00:21:48,539
Give me your passport.
Give it to me. Come on, do it.

261
00:21:48,607 --> 00:21:50,541
I don't think...

262
00:21:50,609 --> 00:21:52,702
You've come a long way,
gentlemen,

263
00:21:52,778 --> 00:21:55,872
but this is no time
for heroes.

264
00:21:55,948 --> 00:21:58,542
I need you to be boys right now.
That's an order.

265
00:21:58,617 --> 00:22:01,882
Get below.
Find your passports.

266
00:22:01,954 --> 00:22:04,184
- Bring 'em on deck.
- [McCrea] All right, let's go.

267
00:22:04,256 --> 00:22:07,225
- On the double!
- Let's go find those little bits.

268
00:22:10,863 --> 00:22:13,127
On deck right now! Come on,
get your stuff. Go, go, go, go!

269
00:22:13,198 --> 00:22:15,132
Don't worry.
Nothing's gonna happen.

270
00:22:15,200 --> 00:22:18,033
Preston, got it? Let's go. Let's get
outta here. Trace! Trace, come on!

271
00:22:18,103 --> 00:22:19,695
- Damn it!
- What?

272
00:22:19,772 --> 00:22:22,935
I can't find my passport.
Oh, no!

273
00:22:23,008 --> 00:22:26,569
Is this your stuff here?
Jesus, what a... Come on, we gotta go.

274
00:22:26,645 --> 00:22:30,411
- I can't find my passport!
- Don't worry about it.
Let's go! Now, damn it!

275
00:22:44,530 --> 00:22:46,464
[Spanish]

276
00:22:46,532 --> 00:22:49,126
- [Spanish]
- He's Puerto Rican.

277
00:22:52,838 --> 00:22:56,467
You know, Captain,

278
00:22:58,711 --> 00:23:02,909
playing cat and mouse
is not very smart.

279
00:23:02,981 --> 00:23:06,508
Not for the mouse. Do you know
you're violating international law...

280
00:23:06,585 --> 00:23:09,611
- by boarding my ship?
- But, you invited us.

281
00:23:09,688 --> 00:23:11,588
- That's bullshit, man.
- Shh.

282
00:23:11,657 --> 00:23:15,286
Your cannons made
a compelling argument.

283
00:23:15,360 --> 00:23:18,329
- [Spanish]
- [McCrea] It's okay. He's got one.

284
00:23:18,397 --> 00:23:20,763
- I've got a passport. I swear to God.
- A stowaway?

285
00:23:20,833 --> 00:23:24,360
He left his passport in Grenada.
It's being mailed to him in Panama.

286
00:23:24,436 --> 00:23:29,373
- I left it last time we boarded.
- That is unfortunate.

287
00:23:33,212 --> 00:23:35,271
We'll have to take him with us.

288
00:23:35,347 --> 00:23:37,781
No! No!

289
00:23:37,850 --> 00:23:39,818
All right, all right, all right.

290
00:23:39,885 --> 00:23:43,548
If he's Cuban,
Castro wears a dress!

291
00:23:43,622 --> 00:23:46,887
All right. Now we've seen
what you can do with a boy.

292
00:23:46,959 --> 00:23:49,860
How would you like to go
a few rounds with a grown-up?

293
00:23:52,231 --> 00:23:54,825
None of my crew
is leaving this ship.

294
00:24:03,809 --> 00:24:05,777
Seventh cavalry.

295
00:24:09,648 --> 00:24:12,242
What are you looking at?

296
00:24:12,317 --> 00:24:16,048
You want to take a souvenir,
you take me.

297
00:24:19,258 --> 00:24:21,249
[Spanish]

298
00:24:27,065 --> 00:24:29,033
[Spanish]

299
00:24:33,038 --> 00:24:36,997
All right, that's it.
Let's move, gentlemen.

300
00:24:42,147 --> 00:24:45,275
Now you will really have something
to teach your students, Captain.

301
00:24:45,350 --> 00:24:48,683
Las estrellas...

302
00:24:48,754 --> 00:24:52,918
es lo unico que un marinero
necessita para navegar.

303
00:24:59,832 --> 00:25:02,096
What'd he say?

304
00:25:02,167 --> 00:25:06,797
He says a real sailor only needs
the stars to navigate with.

305
00:25:06,872 --> 00:25:09,602
[Chuckles]

306
00:25:13,378 --> 00:25:17,474
[Chuck Narrating] And so he guided us
silently through the convoy of warships.

307
00:25:17,549 --> 00:25:19,744
And we later learned they were bound
for a little known destination...

308
00:25:19,818 --> 00:25:22,912
called the Bay of Pigs.

309
00:25:22,988 --> 00:25:25,479
As we rode the trades,
he shared the ancient secrets...

310
00:25:25,557 --> 00:25:29,084
of how to read the waves
and follow the stars.

311
00:25:29,161 --> 00:25:32,528
Panama and the Americas
rose and fell away again.

312
00:25:40,939 --> 00:25:44,102
With the locks of Miraflores
and a continent behind us,

313
00:25:44,176 --> 00:25:46,701
we entered into a new ocean
and a new world...

314
00:25:46,778 --> 00:25:49,941
- that we would stake
and claim as our own.
- [Timer Buzzing]

315
00:25:50,015 --> 00:25:52,643
All right, pens down.

316
00:25:52,718 --> 00:25:55,152
Time's up.
Leave your papers.

317
00:25:55,220 --> 00:25:57,154
[Skipper]
Congratulations, gentlemen.

318
00:25:57,222 --> 00:26:00,988
All hands may go ashore
if you please.

319
00:26:01,059 --> 00:26:05,120
- [Cheering]
- You're on your own. Be careful.

320
00:26:05,197 --> 00:26:07,358
[Skipper]
Buzzer's gone off, Dean.

321
00:26:10,202 --> 00:26:12,693
[Chuck Narrating]
We had traveled over 6,000 miles...

322
00:26:12,771 --> 00:26:15,638
and slipped past the equator
to the very edge of the earth.

323
00:26:15,707 --> 00:26:18,699
Like Darwin before us,
we would see the bliss of nature...

324
00:26:18,777 --> 00:26:20,938
in the absence of man.

325
00:26:21,013 --> 00:26:25,177
It was as if the Albatross
had taken us to another time.

326
00:26:25,250 --> 00:26:29,482
Today I finally understand Homer.
The journey's the thing.

327
00:26:49,207 --> 00:26:52,472
[Shouting]

328
00:27:00,152 --> 00:27:03,087
[Shouting Continues]

329
00:27:38,657 --> 00:27:41,387
Should be a pencil in there.

330
00:27:41,460 --> 00:27:43,223
Hold that.

331
00:27:54,139 --> 00:27:56,403
"Where we go one,

332
00:27:56,475 --> 00:27:58,909
we go all.

333
00:27:58,977 --> 00:28:00,444
Brigantine Albatross.

334
00:28:00,512 --> 00:28:02,571
Nineteen hundred and sixty-one."

335
00:28:02,647 --> 00:28:04,581
That about says it all, huh?

336
00:28:07,386 --> 00:28:10,355
- [Shay] Get in there, guys.
- Chuck Gieg.

337
00:28:10,422 --> 00:28:12,686
Tod Johnstone.

338
00:28:17,763 --> 00:28:19,526
Gil Martin.

339
00:28:20,999 --> 00:28:25,095
Dean Preston.

340
00:28:25,170 --> 00:28:27,263
Tracy Lapchick.

341
00:28:33,845 --> 00:28:36,143
What are they doing?

342
00:28:38,884 --> 00:28:41,546
Claiming their place
in the world.

343
00:28:43,255 --> 00:28:45,985
Why didn't you go?

344
00:28:46,058 --> 00:28:49,619
- I couldn't. It's my watch.
- Uh-uh. I could've stayed.

345
00:28:53,932 --> 00:28:57,561
- Listen. You hear that?
- What?

346
00:28:57,636 --> 00:29:00,571
The sound of an empty ship.

347
00:29:14,453 --> 00:29:18,446
[Boys Chanting]

348
00:29:21,026 --> 00:29:24,325
[Chanting Continues]

349
00:29:41,646 --> 00:29:45,980
[Bell Ringing]

350
00:30:00,098 --> 00:30:03,761
How you doing?

351
00:30:03,835 --> 00:30:05,826
Okay. How'd you do?

352
00:30:07,539 --> 00:30:10,133
730 verbal. 610 math.

353
00:30:10,208 --> 00:30:12,472
Congratulations.

354
00:30:12,544 --> 00:30:14,978
What about you?

355
00:30:25,490 --> 00:30:29,221
- It's 1100!
- [Laughs]

356
00:30:29,294 --> 00:30:31,956
- Dean, you got an 1100! That's great!
- I know.

357
00:30:32,030 --> 00:30:35,522
- [Gil] You know?
- I just can't believe it, you know?

358
00:30:35,600 --> 00:30:38,262
I couldn't have done it
without you guys, though.

359
00:30:38,336 --> 00:30:40,395
- I really couldn't.
- You did.

360
00:30:40,472 --> 00:30:43,566
This is you, Dean.

361
00:30:43,642 --> 00:30:45,576
All you. Nobody else.

362
00:30:45,644 --> 00:30:48,204
Thank you.

363
00:30:50,148 --> 00:30:53,584
You're welcome, stupid.

364
00:30:53,652 --> 00:30:55,745
I'm just testing.

365
00:30:55,820 --> 00:30:59,620
When are you gonna learn,
you little wise ass?

366
00:30:59,691 --> 00:31:02,524
- Here. Thanks.
- Feels different, doesn't it?

367
00:31:03,962 --> 00:31:07,295
What?

368
00:31:07,365 --> 00:31:09,663
Goin' back.

369
00:31:12,871 --> 00:31:16,136
[Sighs]
I don't want it to end. I don't...

370
00:31:17,709 --> 00:31:20,234
wanna be what I was
when I left.

371
00:31:20,312 --> 00:31:23,748
What was that?

372
00:31:23,815 --> 00:31:25,806
Anonymous.

373
00:31:27,852 --> 00:31:31,083
[Sighing]

374
00:31:31,156 --> 00:31:35,183
I've been acing tests
my whole life...

375
00:31:35,260 --> 00:31:37,421
and I still haven't
figured it out.

376
00:31:37,495 --> 00:31:39,963
Figured what out?

377
00:31:40,031 --> 00:31:44,900
- Who I am.
- [Dean] Are you kidding?

378
00:31:44,970 --> 00:31:47,632
I'll tell you who you are.

379
00:31:47,706 --> 00:31:49,833
Glue. You're the glue...

380
00:31:49,908 --> 00:31:53,935
that holds everyone around you
together.

381
00:31:58,016 --> 00:32:00,814
Think I'm gonna choke on
the "feel good."

382
00:32:00,885 --> 00:32:04,184
[Laughing]

383
00:32:29,447 --> 00:32:32,109
[Thunderclaps]

384
00:32:36,554 --> 00:32:38,579
[Radio]
...on the pilot. He needs help.

385
00:32:38,657 --> 00:32:41,626
There goes the umbilical cord
from the Redstone rocket.

386
00:32:41,693 --> 00:32:43,718
We're into countdown.

387
00:32:43,795 --> 00:32:46,889
How are you, Robert?

388
00:32:46,965 --> 00:32:50,025
[Radio]
We're into the two-minute point,
and at this point in the spacecraft...

389
00:32:50,101 --> 00:32:52,968
all the interior cameras
are started.

390
00:32:53,038 --> 00:32:55,006
Two minutes and counting.

391
00:32:55,073 --> 00:32:58,531
Everything is working fine
at the moment.

392
00:32:58,610 --> 00:33:01,704
The radio mikes are now on
in the space capsules.

393
00:33:01,780 --> 00:33:04,578
- Shepard can talk to control.
- Here we go.

394
00:33:04,649 --> 00:33:08,141
- Good luck, huh?
- [Radio] One minute
and 30 seconds to blastoff...

395
00:33:08,219 --> 00:33:11,848
if no further holds
bother us at this point.

396
00:33:14,893 --> 00:33:17,521
The Mercury Control count,
at the last minute you will hear...

397
00:33:17,595 --> 00:33:21,497
Just a moment. I notice that the
cherry picker is being moved through,

398
00:33:21,566 --> 00:33:24,558
- and we are coming up to...
- The morning watch?

399
00:33:24,636 --> 00:33:27,196
- Below.
- [Radio]... countdown,
which you will hear...

400
00:33:27,272 --> 00:33:29,206
in ten-second breaks.

401
00:33:29,274 --> 00:33:31,606
We have just passed
the 92nd mark.

402
00:33:31,676 --> 00:33:33,837
The cherry picker,
the safety device...

403
00:33:33,912 --> 00:33:38,212
[Bell Ringing]

404
00:33:38,283 --> 00:33:42,379
"If you can keep your head while
all about you are losing theirs
and blaming it on you;

405
00:33:42,454 --> 00:33:45,082
if you can trust yourself
when all men doubt you,

406
00:33:45,156 --> 00:33:48,956
but make allowance
for their doubting too."

407
00:33:49,027 --> 00:33:51,120
Morning watch is on!

408
00:33:52,297 --> 00:33:55,698
"Yours is the earth
and everything in it,

409
00:33:55,767 --> 00:33:58,736
which is more,
you'll be a man, my son."

410
00:33:58,803 --> 00:34:02,603
- [Bell Ringing]
- Okay!

411
00:34:02,674 --> 00:34:07,077
- You have fun.
- [Radio] Fifty seconds and counting.

412
00:34:07,145 --> 00:34:09,113
Sweet dreams, Martin.

413
00:34:09,180 --> 00:34:11,648
[Radio]
...has been cut off.

414
00:34:11,716 --> 00:34:13,809
It is now automatically isolated
from the rest of the atmosphere.

415
00:34:13,885 --> 00:34:15,819
It has its own.

416
00:34:15,887 --> 00:34:19,653
[Volume Increased]
The test conductor in the Space
Control Center has taken over.

417
00:34:24,362 --> 00:34:27,695
[Shay]
Bill, Bob, Tim, Charlie, go aloft!

418
00:34:27,766 --> 00:34:30,997
Get those latches closed!

419
00:34:31,069 --> 00:34:33,697
[Radio Continues]

420
00:34:35,039 --> 00:34:37,030
Morning, Shay.

421
00:34:37,942 --> 00:34:40,376
Hey, Tracy.

422
00:34:40,445 --> 00:34:43,312
- Would you trim the main, please?
- Trimming the main!

423
00:34:43,381 --> 00:34:46,612
- North by west.
- North by west.

424
00:34:46,684 --> 00:34:50,313
Get out of here, Bob.
Let the real men take over.

425
00:34:50,388 --> 00:34:54,484
- Looks like we're gonna get wet.
- Yeah, we need it. I'm gonna
take a nice long bath.

426
00:34:54,559 --> 00:34:57,494
- Catch some water for my laundry.
- Save some for me, buddy, huh?

427
00:34:57,562 --> 00:35:00,326
Yeah. Yeah, you got it.

428
00:35:00,398 --> 00:35:01,990
Goin' below!

429
00:35:09,374 --> 00:35:12,343
Everybody okay?
All hands, keep out of the rigging.

430
00:35:16,414 --> 00:35:18,405
Stay clear of the masts.

431
00:35:22,120 --> 00:35:24,748
All right, gentlemen.
Thor's had his fun.

432
00:35:24,823 --> 00:35:27,758
Let's keep a sharp eye.

433
00:35:40,004 --> 00:35:43,030
[Radio]
We're coming up to countdown...

434
00:35:43,107 --> 00:35:45,541
which goes in five seconds.

435
00:35:48,613 --> 00:35:51,446
No, Shay! Dog her down!

436
00:35:51,516 --> 00:35:54,576
- Stay out of the rigging!
- Dog her down!

437
00:36:02,293 --> 00:36:05,057
[Laughing, Cheering]

438
00:36:05,129 --> 00:36:07,791
[Ringing]

439
00:36:10,435 --> 00:36:13,404
- [Alarm Sounding]
- Batten down all hatches!

440
00:36:25,984 --> 00:36:29,010
Skipper!

441
00:36:36,794 --> 00:36:40,059
White squall. Hold tight!

442
00:36:41,065 --> 00:36:43,158
Hold tight!

443
00:37:01,386 --> 00:37:03,980
- [Chuck] Shay!
- [Shay Groans]

444
00:37:04,055 --> 00:37:07,513
- We're losin' it!
- Turn it over!

445
00:37:09,160 --> 00:37:12,254
Look out!
[Screaming]

446
00:37:22,740 --> 00:37:24,799
[Radio]
...agonizingly slowly.

447
00:37:30,214 --> 00:37:33,672
Get outta here!
Get outta here!

448
00:37:33,751 --> 00:37:35,378
Help!

449
00:37:39,223 --> 00:37:41,384
[Tracy]
Tod!

450
00:37:49,767 --> 00:37:53,965
Tod! Tod!
Turn to port!

451
00:38:00,311 --> 00:38:03,474
Turn to port!
Turn to port!

452
00:38:03,548 --> 00:38:08,383
- No! Starboard! Starboard!
- Port, Tod! Port!

453
00:38:08,453 --> 00:38:12,253
Port! Port, damn it!
Turn to port!

454
00:38:19,764 --> 00:38:21,254
Look out!

455
00:38:32,243 --> 00:38:34,677
Leave it, Tod! Get out!

456
00:38:38,850 --> 00:38:40,784
Back! Back!

457
00:38:40,852 --> 00:38:43,719
Come on, Tod. Grab on!

458
00:38:43,788 --> 00:38:46,450
Grab on!

459
00:38:49,861 --> 00:38:51,795
Come on!

460
00:38:51,863 --> 00:38:54,457
Gil, come on. Let's go.
Let's get outta here.

461
00:38:54,532 --> 00:38:58,434
- [Ship Creaking]
- Now, Gil! Come on!

462
00:39:03,708 --> 00:39:06,541
Come on, let's go.

463
00:39:06,611 --> 00:39:09,136
Everybody out!
Keep moving.

464
00:39:12,984 --> 00:39:14,975
We've lost her!

465
00:39:15,053 --> 00:39:18,045
- Free the staysail.
- Yes, sir!

466
00:39:18,122 --> 00:39:20,056
Free the staysail!

467
00:39:20,124 --> 00:39:22,115
Grab a lifeboat.

468
00:39:28,833 --> 00:39:31,597
Skipper!

469
00:39:32,737 --> 00:39:37,003
Right here. Come on, out.
Out this way.

470
00:39:47,919 --> 00:39:51,821
Get out. Anybody in here?

471
00:39:51,889 --> 00:39:54,722
Anybody in here?

472
00:40:08,206 --> 00:40:10,401
Hey!

473
00:40:10,475 --> 00:40:12,966
Get 'em outta there.

474
00:40:24,422 --> 00:40:27,653
Shay!

475
00:41:14,071 --> 00:41:16,039
Sahler!

476
00:41:16,107 --> 00:41:18,632
[Screaming]

477
00:41:19,844 --> 00:41:21,778
[Skipper]
Girard!

478
00:41:21,846 --> 00:41:24,144
Girard!

479
00:41:24,215 --> 00:41:27,275
- [Rings]
- [Radio] America's
fastest traveling man...

480
00:41:28,586 --> 00:41:30,577
[Skipper]
Shay!

481
00:41:31,722 --> 00:41:33,553
Shay!

482
00:41:38,629 --> 00:41:40,824
Girard!

483
00:41:40,898 --> 00:41:43,890
Oh!
[Screaming]

484
00:42:00,651 --> 00:42:02,619
Alice!

485
00:42:10,428 --> 00:42:15,263
Get back, guys!
Get back! She's gonna roll!

486
00:42:15,333 --> 00:42:18,268
- Get in the lifeboat, now!
- Hold on.

487
00:42:56,374 --> 00:42:58,865
Girard!

488
00:42:58,943 --> 00:43:03,539
- Dean!
- Yeah. Yeah. Over here.

489
00:43:03,614 --> 00:43:08,881
[Skipper]
Sahler! Marsh! Gil!

490
00:43:08,953 --> 00:43:11,353
- Gil!
- Where's Gil?

491
00:43:11,422 --> 00:43:14,550
[Screaming]

492
00:43:14,625 --> 00:43:16,889
Help!

493
00:43:19,764 --> 00:43:23,200
One, two, three. Wake up.
One, two, three. Wake up.

494
00:43:23,267 --> 00:43:26,259
- Where's Alice?
- I think they're inside.

495
00:43:26,337 --> 00:43:28,066
Come on!

